# (D4) Single call-site for the Float/Dec type-tag decision, used everywhere a type
# annotation is classified (record fields, fn params, fn return type). Originally each of
# the three call sites ran is_str_float_ty and is_str_dec_ty back to back as two separate
# top-level `if`s; empirically (selfhost_diff/native_resident's SELF fixpoint gate), having
# BOTH of those checks repeated at more than one call site desynced the self-hosted
# compiler's own compile of lumenc.lm from the seed's (a real, narrow self-hosting gap, not
# a Dec-semantics bug -- every corpus program, including decimal.lm, stayed byte-identical
# throughout). Routing every site through one shared helper removes the duplicated shape
# and the fixpoint gate is green again; see native_resident_test.mjs/native_fixpoint_test.mjs.
fn ty_tag(off: Int, len: Int) -> Int {
  if is_str_float_ty(off, len) == 1 { return 1 }
  if is_str_dec_ty(off, len) == 1 { return 2 }
  return 0
}

